# ]po[ Forum
This package is part of ]project-open[, an open-source enterprise project management system.

For more information about ]project-open[ please see:
* [Documentation Wiki](http://www.project-open.com/en/)
* [V5.0 Download](https://sourceforge.net/projects/project-open/files/project-open/V5.0/)
* [Installation Instructions](http://www.project-open.com/en/list-installers)

About ]po[ Forum:

<p><p><p>The ]po[ forum package allows for threaded discussions associated to projects, companies, users and other business objects, effectively converting ]po[ into a online collaboration platform. <p>All forum items are indexed by the <a href="/en/package-intranet-search-pg">full-text search engine</a>, allowing for quick retrieval. <p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /><p>The Forum Module is based on the notion of so called &ldquo;speech acts&rdquo;. Speech acts are elements of the human language that capture how we communication with other persons based on different types of sentences or utterances that we can make. Certain speech acts are mapped to &ldquo;Topic Types&rdquo; in ]project-open[. Each type is designed to support a particular communication model. The following table gives a brief overview about the different types and provides a recommendation on how to use them. <p>

# Online Reference Documentation

## The “Speech Act” Metaphor

<table cellpadding="5" style="width: 100%; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); border-collapse: collapse;"><tbody><tr><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong> Speech Act</strong></td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>Topic Types</strong></td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>Description</strong></td></tr><tr><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> Question</td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> Discussion</td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> A user has a doubt or question and creates a new discussion. The topics treated in a discussion are frequently of interest to a larger number of members.</td></tr><tr><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> Command Tasks</td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> Tasks</td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> A user with supervisor capabilities (project manager, customer, &hellip;) assigns a task to another user and tracks its execution. The assignee can accept or decline the task and inform about the completion of the task. This item is usually used to manage typical &ldquo;To-Do&rdquo; lists. </td></tr><tr><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);&lt;span id=">&quot;&gt; Help!</td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> Incident</td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> An incident is a kind of task that requires immediate action.</td></tr><tr><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> Shout to everybody</td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> News</td><td style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);"> Use the &ldquo;News&rdquo; in order to communicate global information where reading is desirable but not necessary.</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">Did you know&hellip;? </td><td rowspan="1" style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">Note </td><td rowspan="1" style="border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);">Notes are usually project-specific and can be logged by all users. They can consist for example of information gained that ought be tracked </td></tr></tbody></table>
